xian, chengdu and nanjing — have a subway (地铁 dìtiě) system. chongqing has monorail systems. xiamen has a system of bus-only roads, mostly elevated. generally these are modern, clean and efficient. the signs and ticket machines are in both english and chinese. most of these systems are being expanded, and new lines are under construction (as of early 2009) in other cities such as hangzhou, xi'an and chengdu. the long-term plans are quite ambitious, with multiple subway lines per city planned. by 2020 or so china seems likely to have some of the world's most extensive urban transport infrastructure. subway 